pkg/runespacepb/ — vendored RuneSpace protobuf + gRPC stubs
===========================================================

runespace.pb.go, runespace_grpc.pb.go and errors.pb.go are a VERBATIM hard copy
of the generated RuneSpace data-plane stubs. They are NOT generated in this
repo — this SDK vendors them. To update: regenerate in the upstream repo and
re-copy all three .pb.go files plus both reference .proto files, then bump the
commit below.

LOCAL MODIFICATION (ahead of the pin)
-------------------------------------
runespace.pb.go, runespace_grpc.pb.go and proto/runespace/v1/runespace.proto were
updated locally after editing the upstream proto to make GetCentroids a
SERVER-STREAMING RPC: it now returns `stream GetCentroidsChunk` (one
CentroidSetHeader frame, then id-ordered CentroidBatch frames) instead of a single
GetCentroidsResponse, so a large centroid set (nlist*dim floats) transfers without
one oversized message. GetCentroidsResponse was removed; CentroidSetHeader and
CentroidBatch were added. That change is committed on the runespace epic branch as
c23de29 (ahead of the af2b411 pin, not yet on main), so these files are NO LONGER a
verbatim copy of the af2b411 pin. errors.pb.go remains verbatim. Fold into the next
upstream re-pin once the change lands on main.

Additionally re-copied from the runespace `feat/team-based-filter` branch (working
tree, not yet committed/landed) to add the filter-set (team-based) feature:
  - InsertRequest.filter_tags (5) — opaque per-item visibility tag set.
  - SearchRequest.filter_scope (4) — requester's allowed tag scope.
  - GetMetadataRequest.filter_scope (4) — same scope for the resolve-time gate.
  - UpdateTags RPC + UpdateTagsRequest/Response — add/remove an item's tags.
  - CellResult.dead changed from `repeated int64` (position list) to `bytes` (packed
    position bitmap, field renumbered 3->4); the SDK decode moved to a bit test.
Re-pin to the landed commit once this feature merges upstream.

