Data-plane shape at this commit (changed from the prior 1f28fb6 pin)
--------------------------------------------------------------------
  (1) Cluster tier is mandatory — every Insert carries BOTH a flat RMPItem
      {item} and a cluster MMItem {item, cluster_id, centroid_set_version}.
      mm_item is no longer optional (ERROR_REASON_MISSING_MM_ITEM); flat-only
      insert was removed. GetCentroids returns the instance's immutable IVF
      centroid set so the client routes inserts in plaintext.
  (2) Server-side probe selection — SearchRequest carries only the
      L2-normalized plaintext query; fields 2,3 (probe_clusters,
      centroid_set_version) are RESERVED. The server picks the probed clusters
      from the query and forces nprobe from its own config.
  (3) (cell_id, row) result addressing — SearchResponse carries tomb_epoch +
      repeated CellResult rmp + repeated CellResult mm, where CellResult is
      {cell_id, blob, dead}; each tier returns one blob per live cell (RMP/IP0
      and MM/IP1 decode under different CKKS contexts), dead rows co-located per
      blob in that cell's local coordinates. GetMetadata takes rmp_rows +
      mm_rows (both repeated CellRow {cell_id, row}) and returns parallel
      rmp_entries + mm_entries. The earlier single RMPResult / per-cluster
      MMResult{cluster_id} / rmp_slots+MMRow shapes are gone.
  (4) KeyMeta — KeyHeader carries key identity (kid/preset/dim/eval_mode); the
      server persists a KeyMeta (identity + sha256 fingerprint) beside each eval
      key and GetInfoResponse.registered_keys echoes them for cross-verification.
      RegisterKeys is stream-only (RegisterKeysStream{Request,Response}).

